FBIS4-13564 "drnes077_l_94009" FBIS-NES-94-077 Daily Report 17 Apr 1994 ISRAEL Asaf Hefetz Appointed Police Chief Asaf Hefetz Appointed Police Chief TA1704102894 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1000 GMT 17 Apr 94 TA1704102894 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el Hebrew BFN [Text] The cabinet today approved the appointment of Commander Asaf Hefetz as Israel Police Commissioner, to replace Commissioner Rafi Peled. He will assume duty on 1 May and serve a three-year term. Commander Yehuda Wilk, commander of the Jerusalem District Police, announced that he is resigning the force. Speaking to our correspondent earlier today, Commander Wilk said he cannot cooperate with the new police commissioner because their methods of operation are different. Police Minister Shahal told reporters that a very small police officers reshuffle is now expected.
